expression(string_name)
isalnum // true if string_name is a letter or a digit
isalpha // true if string_name is a letter
iscntrl // true if string_name is a control character
isdigit // true if string_name is a digit
isgraph // true if string_name is not a space and printable
islower // true if string_name is a lower case
isprint // true if string_name is a printable character (
        i.e., a space or a character that has a visible
        presentation)
ispunct // true if string_name is a punctuation character (
        i.e., a character that is not a control character, 
        a digit, a letter, or a printable whitespace) 
isspace // true if string_name is a whitespace (i.e., a space, 
        a tab, vertical tab, return, newline, formfeed)
isupper // true if string_name is a upper case
isxdigit// true if string_name is a hexadecimal digit
tolower // If string_name is an uppercase character, it
        will return the character as a lowercase equivalent.
        Otherwise, it will return unchanged.
toupper // If string_name is a lowercase character, it
        will return the character as an uppercase equivalent.
        Otherwise, it will return unchanged.